  "root_text": {
    "iti57:0.1": "Itivuttaka 57 ",
    "iti57:0.2": "Tikanipāta ",
    "iti57:0.3": "Paṭhamavagga ",
    "iti57:0.4": "Dutiyaāsavasutta ",
    "iti57:1.1": "Vuttañhetaṁ bhagavatā vuttamarahatāti me sutaṁ: ",
    "iti57:2.1": "“Tayome, bhikkhave, āsavā. ",
    "iti57:2.2": "Katame tayo? ",
    "iti57:2.3": "Kāmāsavo, bhavāsavo, avijjāsavo—",
    "iti57:2.4": "ime kho, bhikkhave, tayo āsavā”ti. ",
    "iti57:2.5": "Etamatthaṁ bhagavā avoca. ",
    "iti57:2.6": "Tatthetaṁ iti vuccati: ",
    "iti57:3.1": "“Yassa kāmāsavo khīṇo, ",
    "iti57:3.2": "avijjā ca virājitā; ",
    "iti57:3.3": "Bhavāsavo parikkhīṇo, ",
    "iti57:3.4": "vippamutto nirūpadhi; ",
    "iti57:3.5": "Dhāreti antimaṁ dehaṁ, ",
    "iti57:3.6": "jetvā māraṁ savāhinin”ti. ",
    "iti57:4.1": "Ayampi attho vutto bhagavatā, iti me sutanti. ",
    "iti57:4.2": "Aṭṭhamaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "iti57:0.1": "So It Was Said 57 ",
    "iti57:0.2": "The Book of the Threes ",
    "iti57:0.3": "Chapter One ",
    "iti57:0.4": "Defilements (2nd) ",
    "iti57:1.1": "This was said by the Buddha, the Perfected One: that is what I heard. ",
    "iti57:2.1": "“Mendicants, there are these three defilements. ",
    "iti57:2.2": "What three? ",
    "iti57:2.3": "The defilements of sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance. ",
    "iti57:2.4": "These are the three defilements.” ",
    "iti57:2.5": "The Buddha spoke this matter. ",
    "iti57:2.6": "On this it is said: ",
    "iti57:3.1": "“One who has ended the defilement of sensuality, ",
    "iti57:3.2": "whose ignorance has faded away, ",
    "iti57:3.3": "and whose desire to be reborn is finished—",
    "iti57:3.4": "liberated, free of attachments, ",
    "iti57:3.5": "they bear their final body, ",
    "iti57:3.6": "having vanquished Māra with his legions.” ",
    "iti57:4.1": "This too is a matter that was spoken by the Blessed One: that is what I heard. "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "iti57:3.6": "savāhinin”ti → savāhananti (sya-all, pts-vp-pli1) "
  },
